    RTAtomicHIOA_Descriptor

    public class AtomicHIOA_Descriptor
extends AtomicModelDescriptor
    The class AtomicHIOA_Descriptor describes atomic HIOA models in DEVS simulation architectures, associating their URI, their imported and exported event types, their imported and exported variables as well as a factory that can be used to instantiate a model object to run simulations.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant       AtomicModelDescriptor.checkInvariant(this)
 invariant       modelClass == null || AtomicHIOA.class.isAssignableFrom(modelClass)
 invariant       d.importedVariables != null && d.exportedVariables != null

      • createAtomicModel

        public ModelDescriptionI createAtomicModel()
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Description copied from class: AtomicModelDescriptor
        create an atomic model from this descriptor.

        Description

        The creation of an atomic model uses the factory pattern, but when the class M defining the model do not need to change the instantiation protocol (constructor parameters) from the extended abstract classes provided in the library, then only the object representing the class M need to be given and a predefined factory called StandardAtomicModelFactory is automatically used.

        Contract

         pre    true            // no precondition.
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Overrides:
